    "content": "<html>\n<head>\n    <title>Recursion Example</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <h1>Recursion Example</h1>\n    <p>Recursion is a programming technique where a function calls itself repeatedly until it reaches a base case that stops the recursion.</p>\n    <button id=\"run-recursion\">Run Recursion</button>\n\n    <script>\n        function recursiveFunction(n) {\n            if (n === 1) {\n                return;\n            } else {\n                console.log(`Recursive call ${n}: ${recursiveFunction(n - 1)}`);\n            }\n        }\n\n        recursiveFunction(10);\n    </script>\n\n    <script>\n        document.getElementById('run-recursion').addEventListener('click', function() {\n            recursiveFunction(10);\n        });\n    </script>\n</body>\n</html>"
